The paper deals with the stability of queries over databases that accumulate data according to business processes. This topic is closely related to database management (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves decision support. The paper also introduces a formalism that combines control flow and data management, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses different restrictions on the process model and the state of the system, which could be relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
